---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

// AboutPage and Organization Schema for SEO
const aboutSchema = {
	"@context": "https://schema.org",
	"@type": "AboutPage",
	"name": "About Initiative Tracker",
	"description": "Learn about the Initiative Tracker - a free, modern tool for Dungeon Masters to manage D&D 5e combat encounters with AI assistance and 300+ monsters.",
	"mainEntity": {
		"@type": "SoftwareApplication",
		"name": "Initiative Tracker",
		"applicationCategory": "GameApplication",
		"operatingSystem": "Web Browser",
		"offers": {
			"@type": "Offer",
			"price": "0",
			"priceCurrency": "USD"
		},
		"featureList": [
			"Free D&D 5e initiative tracker",
			"AI-powered encounter generation",
			"Drag-and-drop combat management",
			"300+ D&D monsters database",
			"Save and load encounters",
			"Real-time turn tracking",
			"Death saving throws tracking",
			"Status conditions management",
			"Mobile responsive design"
		]
	}
};
---

<Layout 
	title="About - Initiative Tracker for D&D 5e"
	description="Learn about the Initiative Tracker - a free, modern tool for Dungeon Masters to manage D&D 5e combat encounters with AI assistance and 300+ monsters."
>
	<script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(aboutSchema)} />
	<div class="w-full min-h-screen p-4">
		<div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
			<nav class="mb-6 text-sm">
				<a href="/" class="text-primary hover:underline">‚Üê Back to Tracker</a>
			</nav>

			<article class="max-w-none">
				<h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-primary mb-6">About Initiative Tracker</h1>
				
				<p class="text-lg text-muted-foreground mb-8">
					A modern, free initiative tracker built for Dungeon Masters who want to spend less time managing combat and more time creating memorable encounters.
				</p>

				<section class="mb-12">
					<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Our Mission</h2>
					<p class="text-muted-foreground mb-4">
						Running combat in Dungeons & Dragons should be exciting, not overwhelming. As Dungeon Masters, we've all experienced the chaos of managing initiative, tracking hit points, remembering status effects, and looking up monster stats - all while trying to create an engaging battle.
					</p>
					<p class="text-muted-foreground mb-4">
						Initiative Tracker was created to solve this problem. We believe that better tools lead to better games. By automating the tedious parts of combat management, DMs can focus on what matters most: storytelling, tactics, and player engagement.
					</p>
				</section>

				<section class="mb-12">
					<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Why We Built This</h2>
					<p class="text-muted-foreground mb-4">
						After years of DM'ing with pen and paper, spreadsheets, and various online tools, we knew there had to be a better way. Existing initiative trackers were often:
					</p>
					<ul class="list-disc list-inside text-muted-foreground space-y-2 mb-4">
						<li>Too complicated with features that got in the way</li>
						<li>Behind paywalls or subscription models</li>
						<li>Requiring accounts and personal data</li>
						<li>Slow to load with clunky interfaces</li>
						<li>Lacking modern features like AI assistance</li>
						<li>Not mobile-friendly for use at the table</li>
					</ul>
					<p class="text-muted-foreground mb-4">
						We built Initiative Tracker to address all these issues. It's fast, free, privacy-respecting, and packed with genuinely useful features that enhance rather than complicate your game.
					</p>
				</section>

				<section class="mb-12">
					<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">What Makes Us Different</h2>

					<h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6">Completely Free</h3>
					<p class="text-muted-foreground mb-4">
						No subscriptions, no "premium" tiers, no paywalls. Every feature is free forever. We believe great D&D tools should be accessible to everyone, whether you're a veteran DM or running your first game.
					</p>

					<h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6">No Account Required</h3>
					<p class="text-muted-foreground mb-4">
						Start using the tracker immediately with no sign-up, no email, no password. We respect your privacy and don't collect or store personal data. Everything runs in your browser.
					</p>

					<h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6">AI-Powered Without Hassle</h3>
					<p class="text-muted-foreground mb-4">
						Unlike other tools that require you to provide API keys or technical setup, our AI encounter generation works out of the box. Get 20 AI-generated encounters per day with no configuration needed.
					</p>

					<h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6">Modern & Fast</h3>
					<p class="text-muted-foreground mb-4">
						Built with cutting-edge web technology (Astro, React, Tailwind CSS), the tracker loads instantly and responds immediately to your actions. No lag, no waiting.
					</p>

					<h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6">Mobile First</h3>
					<p class="text-muted-foreground mb-4">
						Designed to work perfectly on any device. Use it on your laptop for full features or on your phone for quick reference at the gaming table.
					</p>

					<h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6">Privacy Focused</h3>
					<p class="text-muted-foreground mb-4">
						Your encounters and data never leave your device. No tracking, no analytics, no selling your data. Just a tool that respects your privacy.
					</p>
				</section>

				<section class="mb-12">
					<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Technology Stack</h2>
					<p class="text-muted-foreground mb-4">
						Initiative Tracker is built with modern web technologies:
					</p>
					<ul class="list-disc list-inside text-muted-foreground space-y-2 mb-4">
						<li><strong>Astro:</strong> Ultra-fast static site generation for instant loading</li>
						<li><strong>React:</strong> Powerful, component-based UI for smooth interactions</li>
						<li><strong>Tailwind CSS:</strong> Beautiful, responsive design that works everywhere</li>
						<li><strong>TanStack Table:</strong> High-performance data table for managing combatants</li>
						<li><strong>DND Kit:</strong> Intuitive drag-and-drop functionality</li>
						<li><strong>D&D 5e API:</strong> Monster database from the SRD</li>
					</ul>
					<p class="text-muted-foreground mb-4">
						We leverage cutting-edge web frameworks to deliver a fast, reliable experience for Dungeon Masters worldwide.
					</p>
				</section>

				<section class="mb-12">
					<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">For Dungeon Masters, By Dungeon Masters</h2>
					<p class="text-muted-foreground mb-4">
						Every feature in Initiative Tracker comes from real experience running D&D games. We've DM'd for years across:
					</p>
					<ul class="list-disc list-inside text-muted-foreground space-y-2 mb-4">
						<li>In-person sessions around kitchen tables</li>
						<li>Online games through virtual tabletops</li>
						<li>Convention one-shots with strangers</li>
						<li>Epic long-running campaigns</li>
						<li>Quick pick-up games at game stores</li>
					</ul>
					<p class="text-muted-foreground mb-4">
						We've felt the pain points firsthand and built solutions that actually work at the table. Features aren't added because they sound cool - they're added because they solve real problems that DMs face.
					</p>
				</section>

				<section class="mb-12">
					<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Community & Feedback</h2>
					<p class="text-muted-foreground mb-4">
						Initiative Tracker is constantly evolving based on feedback from the D&D community. We've listened to Dungeon Masters from around the world about what they need, what frustrates them, and what would make their games better.
					</p>
					<p class="text-muted-foreground mb-4">
						Your feedback shapes the future of this tool. Every feature request is considered. Every bug report makes the tracker better. We're building this for you - the DMs who keep the game alive.
					</p>
				</section>

				<section class="mb-12">
					<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Our Values</h2>

					<h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6">Accessibility</h3>
					<p class="text-muted-foreground mb-4">
						Great tools shouldn't be locked behind paywalls. D&D is for everyone, and so are the tools that support it.
					</p>

					<h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6">Simplicity</h3>
					<p class="text-muted-foreground mb-4">
						Complexity doesn't equal quality. We focus on features that genuinely help, not on adding options for the sake of it.
					</p>

					<h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6">Privacy</h3>
					<p class="text-muted-foreground mb-4">
						Your data is yours. We don't collect it, track it, or profit from it. Period.
					</p>

					<h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6">Quality</h3>
					<p class="text-muted-foreground mb-4">
						Every feature is polished and tested. We'd rather have fewer features that work perfectly than many features that work poorly.
					</p>

					<h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6">Community</h3>
					<p class="text-muted-foreground mb-4">
						D&D thrives on community. We listen, adapt, and build based on what DMs actually need.
					</p>
				</section>

			<section class="mb-12">
					<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Legal Stuff</h2>
					<p class="text-muted-foreground mb-4">
						Initiative Tracker is an independent project and is not affiliated with, endorsed by, or sponsored by Wizards of the Coast. Dungeons & Dragons, D&D, their respective logos, and Wizards of the Coast are trademarks of Wizards of the Coast LLC.
					</p>
					<p class="text-muted-foreground mb-4">
						Monster data is sourced from the D&D 5e System Reference Document (SRD) under the Open Gaming License (OGL). This ensures all content is legally available and properly licensed.
					</p>
				</section>

				<section class="mb-12">
					<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Get in Touch</h2>
					<p class="text-muted-foreground mb-4">
						We love hearing from the community! Whether you have:
					</p>
					<ul class="list-disc list-inside text-muted-foreground space-y-2 mb-4">
						<li>Feature suggestions</li>
						<li>Bug reports</li>
						<li>Questions about how to use the tracker</li>
						<li>Stories about epic encounters</li>
						<li>Ideas for improvements</li>
					</ul>
					<p class="text-muted-foreground mb-4">
						Don't hesitate to reach out. Your input helps make Initiative Tracker better for the entire D&D community.
					</p>
				</section>

				<div class="bg-secondary/20 p-6 rounded-lg mt-12">
					<h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Roll Initiative!</h3>
					<p class="text-muted-foreground mb-4">
						Join thousands of Dungeon Masters who've streamlined their combat encounters with Initiative Tracker. Start using it today - no sign-up required.
					</p>
					<a href="/" class="inline-block bg-primary text-primary-foreground px-6 py-3 rounded-lg font-semibold hover:bg-primary/90 transition-colors">
						Start Tracking Initiative
					</a>
				</div>
			</article>
		</div>
	</div>
</Layout>


